Abdomen with gills simple, present on segments I–VIII (all segments with dorsolateral, lateral and ventrolateral gills, except segment I lacking lateral ones) (
Fig. 21
). Segments II–VIII each with pair of long posteromesal setae (those of segments III–VII very thin). Segment IX dorsal sclerite with 6 long setae on its posterior margin and 2 pairs of very short, lateral setae anterior to them; with 2 lateroposterior setae at each side of sclerite (
