For both hollowed twigs and adopted cases, larva building cap of small twigs stuck together with silk threads covering dorsal portion of anterior opening (
Fig. 24
). Most specimens ( 84 %) occupying hollowed-out twigs of different sizes reaching 35 mm in length.

